      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;how-to-publish-a-hugo-site-on-github-pages&#34;&gt;How to Publish a Hugo Site on GitHub Pages&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Publishing a Hugo site on GitHub Pages is a straightforward process. Follow these steps to get your site up and running.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/getting-started/installing/&#34;&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt; installed on your machine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A GitHub account&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Git installed on your machine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-1-create-a-new-hugo-site&#34;&gt;Step 1: Create a New Hugo Site&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First, create a new Hugo site by running the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;hugo new site my-hugo-site
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Replace &lt;code&gt;my-hugo-site&lt;/code&gt; with your desired site name.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <content>&lt;h1 id=&#34;how-to-publish-a-hugo-site-on-github-pages&#34;&gt;How to Publish a Hugo Site on GitHub Pages&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Publishing a Hugo site on GitHub Pages is a straightforward process. Follow these steps to get your site up and running.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/getting-started/installing/&#34;&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt; installed on your machine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A GitHub account&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Git installed on your machine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-1-create-a-new-hugo-site&#34;&gt;Step 1: Create a New Hugo Site&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First, create a new Hugo site by running the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;hugo new site my-hugo-site
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Replace &lt;code&gt;my-hugo-site&lt;/code&gt; with your desired site name.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-2-add-a-theme&#34;&gt;Step 2: Add a Theme&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Navigate to your site directory and add a theme. For example, to add the Ananke theme:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd my-hugo-site
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git init
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git submodule add https://github.com/theNewDynamic/gohugo-theme-ananke.git themes/ananke
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;theme = &amp;#34;ananke&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; config.toml
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-3-create-content&#34;&gt;Step 3: Create Content&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a new post to test your setup:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;hugo new posts/my-first-post.md
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Edit the generated file in &lt;code&gt;content/posts/my-first-post.md&lt;/code&gt; and add some content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-4-build-the-site&#34;&gt;Step 4: Build the Site&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build your site with the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;hugo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The generated files will be in the &lt;code&gt;public&lt;/code&gt; directory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-5-publish-to-github-pages&#34;&gt;Step 5: Publish to GitHub Pages&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;option-1-userorganization-pages&#34;&gt;Option 1: User/Organization Pages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a repository named &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;.github.io&lt;/code&gt; on GitHub.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Push the contents of the &lt;code&gt;public&lt;/code&gt; directory to the repository:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd public
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git init
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git remote add origin https://github.com/&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;.github.io.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git add .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git commit -m &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Initial commit&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git push -u origin master
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;option-2-project-pages&#34;&gt;Option 2: Project Pages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a repository for your project on GitHub.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add the repository as a submodule in the &lt;code&gt;public&lt;/code&gt; directory:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd my-hugo-site
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git submodule add -b gh-pages https://github.com/&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;repository&amp;gt;.git public
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate the site and push to the &lt;code&gt;gh-pages&lt;/code&gt; branch:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;hugo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd public
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git add .
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git commit -m &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Publishing to gh-pages&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git push origin gh-pages
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;conclusion&#34;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your Hugo site should now be live on GitHub Pages. Visit your GitHub Pages URL to see your site in action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy publishing!&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
